LARVA (last instar) (
Figs 59–76
). Body mean length 4.3 mm (SD = 0.2 , n = 5 ); head capsule, lateral mean length 0.4 mm (SD = 0.02 , n = 5 ).

General coloration varying from light to dark grayish green (
Figs 59–62
) (in Carnoy's solution). Head cuticle with small simple setae. Frontoclypeal apotome, in light colored larvae, with positive pattern as in
Figure 63
and, in dark colored larvae, with negative pattern as in
Figure 65
